# Enterprise Model Routing

This project uses multiple AI models.

No single model should be used for every task.

Always choose the model that provides the best balance between:

- Accuracy
- Reliability
- Speed
- Cost
- Context size
- Reasoning quality

Model routing is intentional.

Never choose a model randomly.

---

# Routing Principles

Always use the least expensive model capable of completing the task with the required quality.

Escalate only when necessary.

Never use the strongest model for simple work.

---

# Preferred Models

Current project preference:

Primary Architecture Model

- Claude Opus 4.7

Primary Research Model

- GPT-5.5

Primary Implementation Model

- Composer 2.5

These preferences may change as better models become available.

---

# GPT-5.5 Routing

Prefer GPT-5.5 for:

- Research
- Planning
- Web Search
- Documentation Analysis
- Technical Comparison
- API Research
- Framework Research
- Official Documentation
- Mathematics
- Algorithms
- Architecture Review
- Design Review
- Requirement Analysis

Use GPT whenever current knowledge is important.

Combine with:

- Context7 MCP
- Fetch MCP
- OpenAPI MCP

---

# Claude Opus Routing

Prefer Claude Opus for:

- Enterprise Architecture
- System Design
- Domain Modeling
- Large Refactoring
- Complex Business Logic
- Code Review
- Technical Debt Analysis
- Design Decisions
- Security Review
- Architecture Evolution

Use Opus whenever deep reasoning is more important than speed.

---

# Composer 2.5 Routing

Prefer Composer 2.5 for:

- CRUD implementation
- Boilerplate generation
- Repetitive code
- Unit tests
- Integration tests
- DTO generation
- API implementation
- UI implementation
- Component generation
- Simple refactoring
- Documentation drafting

Use Composer 2.5 whenever implementation speed is the priority.

---

# Escalation Policy

Escalate from Composer 2.5 to GPT or Opus when:

- Requirements become ambiguous.
- Architecture changes.
- Business logic becomes complex.
- Security is involved.
- Multiple systems interact.
- Refactoring spans many modules.
- The implementation repeatedly fails.

---

# Downgrade Policy

After planning is complete:

Move implementation back to the implementation model.

Avoid keeping expensive models active for repetitive work.

---

# Cost Optimization

Use premium models only when they provide measurable value.

Prefer inexpensive models for:

- Formatting
- Documentation
- Small edits
- Simple implementations
- Repetitive changes

---

# Context Optimization

Use the smallest context that solves the task.

Avoid loading unnecessary files.

Avoid unnecessary MCP servers.

Avoid unnecessary Rules.

